"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-news-world-1886296-River-Seine-unsafe-for-Olympics-ecoli\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  A charity has raised concerns the Seine in Paris could be \\\"unsafe for the Olympics\\\" due to the \\\"alarming\\\" levels of E.coli bacteria found in the water.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 36, \"end\": 41, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999989095159, \"rank\": 1.0903502586757279e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 45, \"end\": 50, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.484792811421076e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The huge 777-km river, which cuts through Paris, is set to stage several Olympic swimming events in around 100 days times.\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 197, \"end\": 202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.484792811421076e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Surfrider Foundation, a French water charity, says it has taken 14 samples over a six-month period and found the water to be potentially dangerous in all but one.\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 287, \"end\": 307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfrider_Foundation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Surfrider Foundation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfrider_Foundation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Surfrider_Foundation\"}, {\"begin\": 311, \"end\": 317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9803782474139721, \"rank\": 0.018170471014156288, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The charity penned on open letter saying it \\\"wanted to share with stakeholders ... rising concerns about the quality of the Seine but also the risks faced by athletes moving in contaminated water\\\".\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999989095159, \"rank\": 1.0903502586757279e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:Paris brings back swimming in the Seine after 100 years    French authorities have committed to a huge clean up of the river before the Olympic beging on July 26.\", \"from\": 650, \"to\": 824, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 662, \"end\": 667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.484792811421076e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999989095159, \"rank\": 1.0903502586757279e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9803782474139721, \"rank\": 0.018170471014156288, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Seine is set to play a big part in the games, providing the backdrop for the opening ceremony and hosting swimming events and the triathlon.\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999989095159, \"rank\": 1.0903502586757279e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have spent around \\u20ac1.4 billion (\\u00a31.2 billion) on upgrading the sewage system and stormwater treatment facilities in Paris to clean the water ahead of the games.\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 1136, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1092, \"end\": 1097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.484792811421076e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It came after three test events in 2023 had to be cancelled due to the levels of E.coli found in the water,reports Le Monde.\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1262, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1219, \"end\": 1225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"E.coli\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Escherichia_coli\"}, {\"begin\": 1253, \"end\": 1261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Monde\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfrider said tests were carried out by the laboratory Eau de Paris and environmental analysis group Analy-Co from September to March under the bridges Alexandre-III and l'Alma, where the Olympics sports are to take place.\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1320, \"end\": 1332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eau de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfrider said tests had been carried out by the laboratory Eau de Paris and environmental analysis group Analy-Co from September to March underneath the bridges Alexandre-III and l'Alma, where the Olympics sports are to take place.\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1721, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eau de Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eau_de_Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:Putin sets his sights on Olympics as Macron says Russia will target Paris  Do not miss:Charles accused of snubbing Macron as he's still not been invited to key event  Do not miss:French Olympic diver slips off board in front of President before Paris 2024    It said readings showed levels of both E. coli and enterococci bacteria were often double, sometimes even three times, higher than maximum European amounts allowed.\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 2158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.219041487536144e-18, \"text\": \"Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}, {\"begin\": 1772, \"end